## `test_interop_rsync_preserves_metadata(mount, tmp_path)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-interop-3 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: external tool behavior -->

### Postconditions

```python
if not HAS_RSYNC:
    pytest.skip("rsync not installed")

# Seed an external directory with files of specific mode + mtime.
src = tmp_path / "src"
src.mkdir()
(src / "a.txt").write_text("aaa")
(src / "b.txt").write_text("bbb")
os.chmod(src / "a.txt", 0o640)
os.utime(src / "a.txt", (1_000_000_000, 1_000_000_000))

# rsync into the mount.
subprocess.run(
    ["rsync", "-a", f"{src}/", str(mount)],
    check=True,
)

# mtime preserved within a second; mode preserved exactly.
st = os.stat(mount / "a.txt")
assert st.st_mode & 0o777 == 0o640
assert abs(st.st_mtime - 1_000_000_000) < 1
```

