## `test_interop_tar_round_trip(mount, tmp_path)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-interop-4 -->
<!-- trace: skipped -->
<!-- trace_skip_reason: external tool behavior -->

### Postconditions

```python
if not HAS_TAR:
    pytest.skip("tar not installed")

# Seed tree in mount.
(mount / "a").mkdir()
(mount / "a" / "f1").write_bytes(b"one")
(mount / "a" / "f2").write_bytes(b"two")

# Tar it out of the mount, back into a plain dir.
archive = tmp_path / "out.tar"
subprocess.run(
    ["tar", "-cf", str(archive), "-C", str(mount), "a"],
    check=True,
)

restore = tmp_path / "restore"
restore.mkdir()
subprocess.run(
    ["tar", "-xf", str(archive), "-C", str(restore)],
    check=True,
)

assert (restore / "a" / "f1").read_bytes() == b"one"
assert (restore / "a" / "f2").read_bytes() == b"two"
```

